text: William Joseph "Bill" Rosendahl (May 15, 1945 â€“ March 30, 2016) was an American politician. He served on the Los Angeles City Council. He represented Council District 11 from 2005 to 2013. He was a member of the Democratic Party. Rosendahl was openly gay. Rosendahl died at his home in Mar Vista, Los Angeles of ureteral cancer on March 30, 2016 at the age of 70. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:2016 deaths Category:Gay men Category:LGBT people from California Category:Politicians from Los Angeles Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians
